Me Matt and Kevin went cruisin on Speedway tonight. We just got back and raced a couple cars.

1st encounter was a Mistubishi EVOVIII, some jackassw as driving it swerving in and out of traffic, couldn't really race him but wanted to. 2nd encounter was some kind of old Buick Regal V6 Turbo. This car was one fast fucking old grandma car. We saw it accelerate away from us and it totally took us off guard cause it looked like a piece of crap. So we catch a light with him and we both gun it, I pull ahead right away and he stays with me at about my rear bumper. I couldn't believe he was hanging with me. But at about 75mph I pulled away from him and shut down at 100mph and won. Then we saw a cop pull someone over and we freaked out and left speedway. But on the way back we meet out 3rd encounter, a riced out Honda Prelude with a body kit. He didn't want to race but then I noticed next to the Prelude was our 4th encounter: another SRT-4. It was black, looked stock but it had a Blow-Off Valve. So all the way down 1st Ave we tried running against it but we couldnt get organized so eventually we both stopped in the middle of the road and decided to catch a light. After a lot of failed attempts at racing we finalyl caught a good light and raced. I had Matt and Kevin, an extra 300-ish lbs in my car. So we both floor it and we are dead even he starts pulling on me, but then I regain traction and pull on him leaving him at my rear bumper. I stay ahead until 105mph. Then we both turn into Best Buy on 1st Ave and talk about our cars, it was pretty cool.

So yeah that was it, it was so much fun, I dropped about 1/3 of my gas but oh well, haha.

I got like $250 back, haha nice. I think I'm spending it on putting money back into the bank that I spent like weeks and weeks ago anticipating an extra $250. Although PSP's are $250 and those are sweet. Maybe I'll just use it or my car payment, or part of it at least. An iPod would be nice...

I think I almost got shanked by a bum.

So me Matt, Andrew, and Kevin were hanging outside peter piper at around midnight. Nevermind what we were doing, but all of the sudden a bum on a bike with a backpack and a full half-gray beard  rides up to us in a coarse voice "Hey do you guys have any change I can have?"

I gave him 86 cents. Nobody else had anything. So he kept pleading with us for money. Then he was like hey I'll give you guys free newpapers every day I really need the money I want to buy a 40. He sells newspapers on the corner.

Time goes by he won't leave it's been like 30 minutes. By now he's getting into his days in 1980 when he was a Platoon Leader in the Marines in the Afganistan/Russian conflict. This guy was really fucked up, several times he had to kill women and children with bombs strapped to their chest. He's telling us in great detail how it was like in the war.

So he finalyl gets off his bike and puts us into a situational skit. He comes about an inch from ym face his breath reaking of whiskey: "Let's say this guy here (andrew) is an afgani women. You check her for weapons and you see that she's completely wired with explosives... what do you do?"

"Well I guess I have to shoot ya, Andrew sorry! Lol"

Big mistake.

"You think that's funny boy? If you were in my platoon I would shoot you righ in the head. Boom, your gone. This is nothing to laugh about! Look in my eyes (his pupils were almost non-exostant lol) you don't know shit. I have had to kill peopel with my bare hands like this <mimes a neck breaking>"

<gulp> sorry?

He goes on for another 15 mins about hes haunted by his past and matt, andrew and kevin are all either freaked out, laughing, or trying to stay calm. Cause this guy was drunk he coulda done anything.

He had 2 bullet wounds and 3 or 4 knife scars on his arms. He told me I would make a great fighter pilot. Ok...

It may not sound liek much but if you were there you would agree this was by far, the craziest, drunkest, most fucked up bum ever. I'm leaving a lto of stuff out but I'm not going to go on cause he talked to us for a good 45-60 mins.

10. Resident Evil 2 - Playstation
It was hard, very hard. But oh my god if any of you guys played this at 12 like me you would have shit your pants. This game was so scary it was a rush.

9. Contra - Nintendo
This is an Old ass game, I played it with my cousin when I was like 7 and I still find it fun. It's the game that started all shooting games. But again this is another really really hard game.

8. Sonic (All except Sonic Shuffle) - Dreamcast, Genesis, etc.
Ok I grew up on this game, Sonic 1,2,3 3-D, Pinball, Racing, Adventure, Adventure 2, I probably missed a couple. Every sonic game I've ever played I've got my money's worth. Except for Sonic Shuffle but that game was $10.

7. Legend of Zelda: Ocarina Of Time - Nintendo 64
I spent hours as a kid ont his game. This game was great because it stayed fun the entire time even though it was difficult. The reason its so great to me is I can't think of anything to make the game better. It's close to perfection!

6. Warcraft III - PC
I still play this game and it's really fun. It constantly changes everday and the game never gets old. It's probably the dorkiest game on the list though rofl...

5. Wave Race 64 - Nintendo 64
Ok none of you guys probably agree with me but I LOVED this game!!!! When it came out the graphics were unrivaled and the physics were dead on. It's my faavorite racing game of all time..... I just soiled myself.

4. Goldeneye 007 - Nintendo 64
If you don't like this game then you probably are either gay, or you are a girl. This is the best shooting game. Ever. EVER.

3. Soul Calibur - Dreamcast
The best fighting game ever. EVER. Ok I'll stop doing that.

2. Super Punchout - Super Nintendo
Hmmm... this game... is... so.. great. If this game never existed I would probably be smoking crack in an ally in Miami. This game is always fun. I wish, I wish so much they'd make a Gamecube Version or something. Well this game USED to be hard but I can beat it in under a half hour. I dont coutn it as a fighting game cause it's in a league of it's own. I cant even explain how good tis game is to me.

1. Super Mario 64 - Nintendo 64
I got this when I was 12. It chanegd my life. No not really but it's my favorite game of all. There are so many levels, so many stars to get, so many bosses to kill, mini games, everything. This game is the best game ever made in my opinion. It was worth it alone buying a Nintendo 64.

 

Hey let me know what you guys think. For the most part it's a pretty solid list except for a few games that are personal favorites. I'm gonna go play punchout.
